article.description:
Katie Smith scored 27 points, including five
3-pointers, to lead the Minnesota Lynx to a 78-60 win over the
Washington Mystics on Saturday night.
article.headline: Minnesota avenges previous week's loss in D.C.
article.linkText: Smith hits five 3s in leading Lynx past Mystics
article.story:
MINNEAPOLIS (AP) -- Katie Smith scored 27 points, including five
3-pointers, to lead the Minnesota Lynx to a 78-60 win over the
Washington Mystics on Saturday night.

Svetlana Abrosimova added 13 points and six rebounds for the
Lynx (4-3), who avenged last week's loss to the Mystics.

"When [Smith]'s hitting, everyone can relax and shoot the
ball," she said. "We have a sense of confidence when we step on
the floor now. Our chemistry has improved tremendously."

Alana Beard led Washington (3-6) with 19 points and five
rebounds and DeLisha Milton-Jones had 10 points.

The Mystics led 32-30 at halftime until Smith's 3-pointer
sparked an 8-0 run. Beard helped cut the deficit to 40-39 with a
jump shot, a fast-break layup and a 3-pointer.

Washington's Temeka Johnson added two free throws to give the
Mystics their last lead.

Abrosimova's driving layup and 3-point play then started a 26-7
Lynx run. It featured four 3-pointers, including back-to-back 3s
from Stacey Lovelace-Tolbert and Amber Jacobs, that gave the Lynx a
64-45 lead with 6:52 left.

"They really executed their offense well and pounded us on the
boards. ... Next thing we know, it's up to 18 and that's it."

Smith made 5-of-8 from 3-point range, and Minnesota finished
10-of-17 from beyond the arc.

Minnesota's Vanessa Hayden left the game with 4:53 remaining in
the first half when she turned her right ankle.
